    "plan": "# Plan — Trim orbit.graph.* tool surface\n\n> **Related:** Tool-description rewrites were split into T20260423-0525 (pure-text change, ships independently). That task supersedes the original Step 2 of this plan. The schema-size baseline (Step 1 below) should be taken AFTER T-0525 lands so description savings are attributed to T-0525, not to this task.\n\n## Ordering rationale\n\nThe changes are sequenced lowest-risk → highest-risk so that regression signal from early steps informs later steps, and so the schema-size measurement (AC#7) has a clean baseline before any shape changes land.\n\nEach step below ends in a green `cargo test -p orbit-tools` so partial progress is always landable.\n\n## Step 1 — Baseline measurement + schema-size harness\n\n**Goal:** make AC#7 (≥25% schema-size reduction) measurable from day one.\n\n**Precondition:** T20260423-0525 (description rewrite) has landed. Baseline is measured against the post-T-0525 state so this task's reduction budget targets shape changes, not wording.\n\n- Add `crates/orbit-tools/tests/graph_schema_size.rs` (integration test). It iterates every `Tool` whose `schema().name.starts_with(\"orbit.graph.\")`, serializes each `ToolSchema` via `serde_json::to_string`, and sums the byte count.\n- The test prints the total to stdout and asserts the sum is below a `MAX_BYTES` constant. On first commit, set `MAX_BYTES` to the current total so the test passes; subsequent commits lower it as shape changes land.\n- Capture the baseline number in the PR description; final PR shows before/after with ≥25% delta.\n\n**Files:** new `crates/orbit-tools/tests/graph_schema_size.rs`, one const.\n\n**Verify:** `cargo test -p orbit-tools graph_schema_size` prints the baseline and passes.\n\n## Step 2 — `orbit.graph.pack` signature-only default (AC#4)\n\n**Goal:** simplest shape change — an input default flip with a new branch in the execution path.\n\n- Add `summary: bool` param (default `true`) to the schema in `knowledge_pack.rs`.\n- In `execute`, if `summary` is true, walk the packed response and strip body text from each entry, keeping `{name, kind, file, line, signature}` only. A helper in `orbit_knowledge::store::pack` (if one fits naturally) is acceptable; otherwise inline in the tool.\n- Unit test: fixture graph with one impl block; assert response JSON for the default call does NOT contain the impl body string, and that `summary: false` DOES.\n\n**Files:** `crates/orbit-tools/src/builtin/orbit/knowledge_pack.rs`, possibly a small helper in `crates/orbit-knowledge/src/store/pack.rs`.\n\n**Verify:** new unit test passes; schema-size test still green.\n\n## Step 3 — `orbit.graph.refs` output partitioning (AC#3)\n\n**Goal:** shape the response into `{code_refs, doc_refs, config_refs}`. This is the highest-value single change from the ISSUES.md evidence (the `AgentRuntime` refs call returned doc + code mixed).\n\n- In `knowledge_refs.rs`, classify each ref by its node's location: `*.rs|*.py|*.ts|…` → `code_refs`; `*.md|*.txt|docs/` → `doc_refs`; `*.yaml|*.toml|*.json|config/` → `config_refs`. Centralize the classifier as a small helper (`fn classify_ref_kind(path: &Path) -> RefKind`) co-located with the tool.\n- Add an `include: Vec<String>` optional param defaulting to `[\"code\"]`. If the caller passes `[\"code\",\"doc\",\"config\"]` or `[\"all\"]`, include all three.\n- Response shape: always the top-level keys `{code_refs, doc_refs, config_refs}`, but `doc_refs` and `config_refs` are `[]` unless requested.\n- Add per-file cap: no single file contributes more than `per_file_limit` (default 5) refs in any category.\n- Unit test: fixture graph where a selector has 3 code refs, 2 doc refs, 1 config ref. Assert default call returns `code_refs: [3 items], doc_refs: [], config_refs: []`. Assert `include: [\"all\"]` returns all three populated.\n\n**Files:** `crates/orbit-tools/src/builtin/orbit/knowledge_refs.rs`, test fixtures.\n\n**Verify:** new unit test passes; schema-size test still green.\n\n## Step 4 — `orbit.graph.search` ranking (AC#1, AC#10)\n\n**Goal:** code symbols rank above non-code hits when filters are unset.\n\n- In `knowledge_search.rs`, when `type`/`kind`/`prefix` are all absent, wrap results with a rank key: code symbols (kind in `{function, method, struct, trait, impl, class, interface, field, module}`) get rank 0; file-path matches get rank 1; non-code nodes (YAML/MD/TOML by extension) get rank 2.\n- Sort stable-by-rank before applying `limit`.\n- Add `include_non_code: bool` default `false`. When false AND no explicit filters, drop non-code results entirely from the response (don't just deprioritize — remove, so the `limit` window isn't polluted).\n- Unit test: fixture graph with one `trait AgentRuntime` symbol and one `benchmarks/graph/tasks/locate-agentruntime.yaml` file node. Query `AgentRuntime`, default params; assert the symbol is the top-1 result and the YAML node is absent from the response.\n- Smoke test for AC#10: after Step 4 lands, run `orbit tool run orbit.graph.search --input '{\"query\":\"AgentRuntime\",\"limit\":5}'` against the live orbit workspace and capture the output in the PR description.\n\n**Files:** `crates/orbit-tools/src/builtin/orbit/knowledge_search.rs`, unit test, a `rank_by_kind` helper.\n\n**Verify:** new unit test passes; smoke test output recorded.\n\n## Step 5 — `orbit.graph.overview` decision gate (AC#2, AC#6)\n\n**Goal:** resolve the keep-or-remove question explicitly.\n\n- Before implementing, write a short note at the top of the PR description: \"Decision: keep / deprecate. Reason: …\"\n- Recommended default based on ISSUES.md evidence: **keep but flip the default to `format: \"summary\"` when the query scope is unbounded OR contains > 20 files.** The current tool already supports a summary mode; the change is the default behavior.\n- Implement: in `knowledge_overview.rs::OverviewFormat::parse`, when `format` is not provided, compute file count for the requested scope; if > 20 or scope is unbounded, return `Summary`; otherwise `Full`. Keep the existing `FILE_THRESHOLD = 50` auto-compact behavior as an additional backstop.\n- Unit test: fixture graph with 25 files, call with no prefix and no format; assert response does not contain per-file symbol arrays (i.e. is the summary shape).\n- If the implementing agent decides to deprecate instead: remove from the registry in `builtin/orbit/mod.rs`, delete `knowledge_overview.rs`, add a migration hint to the `orbit-graph` skill doc, and note the removal in the PR description. Skip the unit test above; instead add a test asserting the tool is NOT registered.\n\n**Files:** `crates/orbit-tools/src/builtin/orbit/knowledge_overview.rs`, tests.\n\n**Verify:** new unit test passes; schema-size test ideally shows a meaningful drop here.\n\n## Step 6 — Skill doc sync (AC#9)\n\n- Open `crates/orbit-core/assets/skills/orbit-graph/SKILL.md` and verify every command example still matches the new tool shapes. In particular:\n  - If `overview` default changed to summary, flag any example that assumes full output.\n  - Update `refs` examples to show `include: [\"code\"]` is the default — no flag needed — and show the opt-in for `include: [\"all\"]`.\n  - Update `pack` examples to note signature-only by default; full bodies via `summary: false`.\n  - Update `search` examples to mention that code symbols rank first by default.\n- Re-run any script in the skill to confirm it still produces valid output on the living workspace.\n\n**Files:** `crates/orbit-core/assets/skills/orbit-graph/SKILL.md`.\n\n**Verify:** manual read; at least one example command executed end-to-end against the live workspace.\n\n## Step 7 — Final checks (AC#7, AC#8)\n\n- Re-measure schema size; lower `MAX_BYTES` in Step 1's test to the final value. Confirm ≥25% reduction vs. baseline. Record before/after in PR description.\n- Run `make build` and `make fmt` from repo root.\n- Run `cargo test -p orbit-tools -p orbit-knowledge`.\n- Run the AC#10 smoke test one more time; record the top result and confirm it is a code symbol.\n\n## Note on AC#5\n\nAC#5 (\"every graph tool's description begins with `Use when` and contains a `Prefer over grep when` clause\") is satisfied by T20260423-0525. If T-0525 has landed by the time this task starts, AC#5 is already green — include a one-line `git show` citation in the PR description. If T-0525 has not landed, either block on it or re-assert AC#5 here.\n\n## Risks and mitigations\n\n- **MCP clients pinning the old `overview` shape.** The living harness (`benchmarks/graph/`) and frozen snapshots (`benchmarks/graph_v1/`) both run against whatever is in `crates/`. If Step 5 deprecates `overview`, any external skill or doc that references it must be found via grep before landing. Mitigation: `grep -r \"orbit.graph.overview\" --include=\"*.md\" --include=\"*.yaml\" --include=\"*.rs\"` before the final commit.\n- **`refs` partitioning changes the response shape unconditionally.** Consumers expecting the old flat list will break. Mitigation: the change is the whole point, but call it out in the PR description and in the skill doc; the v1 frozen harness is unaffected because it doesn't re-run.\n- **Schema-size baseline timing.** If Step 1 is taken before T-0525 lands, this task will claim T-0525's savings as its own. Mitigation: Step 1 is gated on T-0525 being merged.\n\n## Out-of-scope checkpoints\n\n- Tool-description rewrites (T20260423-0525).\n- Indexer-side exclusion via `.orbitignore` (T20260423-0452) — complementary but independent.\n- Adding new graph tools. This task is scope reduction + shape fixes only.\n- `aggregate.py` utilization column (T20260423-0524).",
