    "description": "## Problem\n\nThe knowledge-graph indexer at `crates/orbit-knowledge/src/pipeline/scan.rs` filters files using `git check-ignore --stdin` only (see `git_ignored_paths` at line 78). Files that are committed to git but should not be indexed have no exclusion path.\n\nThe motivating case is the frozen benchmark snapshot committed as part of T20260422-1609: `benchmarks/graph_v1/runs/` contains 373 per-run JSON records and JSONL transcripts (~6 MB) that are tracked in git for reproducibility (see `benchmarks/CONVENTIONS.md` §\"Runs and git\"). Without a second-layer filter, these files reach the parser and pollute the graph.\n\nThis pollution was directly observed in v1: `orbit.graph.search \"AgentRuntime\"` returned `benchmarks/graph/tasks/locate-agentruntime.yaml` config keys *before* code symbols — evidence captured in `benchmarks/graph_v1/ISSUES.md`.\n\n## Why It Matters\n\n- **Graph quality.** Transcript strings produce thousands of spurious symbols/refs that dilute search ranking and bloat the store.\n- **Parse time.** Every full reindex reparses the frozen artifacts; they are append-only and never change.\n- **Gates v2 benchmark design.** The next round of graph benchmark fixtures (see `benchmarks/graph_v1/RESULTS.md` §Recommendations #4) will add navigation-heavy tasks whose ground truth assumes search does not return benchmark noise. Without this filter, v2 measurements would partly be measuring indexer noise rather than graph-tool utility.\n- **User extensibility.** Workspaces with committed-but-non-code artifacts (test fixtures, golden files, captured API responses) need a supported way to opt out of indexing without having to gitignore them.\n\n## Proposal\n\nIntroduce `.orbitignore` — a gitignore-compatible exclusion file that the knowledge-graph indexer consults before queueing files for parse. Semantics match gitignore (`**` globs, negation `!pattern`, directory-only `foo/`, `#` comments). Nested `.orbitignore` files in subdirectories compose with the root file.\n\nUse the `ignore` crate (same as ripgrep) to get battle-tested, gitignore-compatible pattern logic without hand-rolling. This dependency belongs in `orbit-knowledge` per the architecture diagram in `CLAUDE.md`.\n\n## Layer Separation\n\n`.orbitignore` is NOT the same as policy `denyRead` / `denyModify`:\n\n| Layer | Purpose | When evaluated |\n|---|---|---|\n| `.orbitignore` | Indexer inclusion — controls what enters the knowledge graph | At parse/scan time |\n| Policy `denyRead` / `denyModify` | Runtime FS access at activity execution | At tool-call time |\n\nBoth can reference the same path but answer different questions. Docs must make this separation explicit so users don't conflate them.\n\n## Constraints / Notes\n\n- Lives in `orbit-knowledge` (the pipeline crate). Per `CLAUDE.md`, that crate depends on `orbit-common` only and has no downstream code-path back into the deny-layer, so the separation is structural.\n- Default ignore set should ship out-of-box: at minimum `target/`, `node_modules/`, `.orbit/`. Users should not have to boilerplate these.\n- Incremental reindex after `.orbitignore` changes: adding a pattern that excludes a previously-indexed path must remove that path's nodes on the next pipeline run without requiring a full rebuild. Removing a pattern must re-admit the path.\n- This task is feature work, not friction. It is authored from a user-visible gap (benchmark-run pollution is observable in `graph.search` output), not an agent self-report.\n- Ownership: `claude` owns `docs/design/knowledge-graph/` per `CLAUDE.md`. The layer-separation doc section goes there.",
    "execution_summary": "## Status\nsuccess\n\n## Summary of Changes\nImplemented scan-time `.orbitignore` support in `orbit-knowledge` using the `ignore` crate, with built-in defaults plus root and nested `.orbitignore` composition. Added unit coverage in `crates/orbit-knowledge/src/pipeline/scan.rs` and integration coverage in `crates/orbit-knowledge/tests/orbitignore.rs` for literal matches, recursive globs, negation, directory-only rules, comments, default ignores, nested composition, and incremental reindex removal.\n\nAdded workspace-root `.orbitignore` seeding during `orbit workspace init` in `crates/orbit-cli/src/command/workspace.rs`, backed by a shared default template exported from `crates/orbit-knowledge/src/lib.rs`, while preserving existing user-authored `.orbitignore` files.\n\nUpdated `docs/design/knowledge-graph/2_design.md`, `4_decisions.md`, and `references/glossary.md` to document the new scan-time inclusion layer and its separation from runtime policy access.\n\n## Strategic Decisions\n- Keep `.orbitignore` scan-time behavior in `orbit-knowledge` and keep runtime access control in `orbit-policy`. | Rationale: preserves the architecture boundary and avoids coupling graph refresh to tool-call policy decisions.\n- Seed a visible workspace-root `.orbitignore` during `orbit workspace init` while preserving any existing file. | Rationale: users can discover and customize the defaults without reading source, but existing local intent is never overwritten.\n\n## Overall Assessment\nThe change is complete and verified. Search pollution from benchmark artifacts is removed by the new scan-time exclusion layer, default exclusions are visible/editable from workspace initialization onward, and the docs now describe the boundary between graph inclusion and runtime access control.\n\n## Verification\n- `make fmt`\n- `cargo test -p orbit-cli workspace_init`\n- `cargo test -p orbit-knowledge orbitignore`\n- `cargo test -p orbit-knowledge`\n- `make build`\n- `cargo build -p orbit-cli`\n- `target/debug/orbit workspace init --no-mcp` in a temp workspace to confirm seeded `.orbitignore` contents\n- `./target/debug/orbit graph build --root /Users/daniel/workspace/repos/orbit/.orbit --repo /Users/daniel/.codex/worktrees/430c/orbit --ref worktree-430c`\n- `./target/debug/orbit tool run orbit.graph.search --root /Users/daniel/workspace/repos/orbit/.orbit --full --input '{\"query\":\"AgentRuntime\",\"type\":\"symbol\",\"limit\":10,\"ref\":\"worktree-430c\",\"agent\":\"codex\",\"model\":\"gpt-5\"}'`\n\nThe final `orbit.graph.search` output returned only code symbols under `crates/orbit-agent/...` and no `benchmarks/**` hits.\n\n## Artifacts\n- Commit: `56117f6c` (`[T20260423-0452] Add .orbitignore scan exclusions and init seeding`)\n- Branch: `codex/t20260423-0452-orbitignore`\n",
