    "description": "## Problem\nWe need a real end-to-end QA pass for the PR-based `orbit run ship` workflow using a disposable mock task, executed from a clean secondary worktree rather than this dirty checkout.\n\n## Why It Matters\n`orbit run ship` is a high-impact workflow: it selects tasks, creates a shared worktree, invokes the implementer, pushes a branch, and opens a PR. We need current evidence that the workflow still behaves correctly in a realistic run, plus an auditable record of what happened.\n\n## Constraints / Notes\n- Run the QA from a separate git worktree rooted at the current HEAD.\n- Point Orbit commands in that worktree back to this repository's canonical `.orbit` root so task state stays authoritative.\n- Use a clearly-labeled mock task whose product-surface change is disposable and easy to identify.\n- Record the exact commands, worktree path, job run IDs, task status transitions, PR outcome, and any cleanup performed in the execution summary.\n- If the workflow is clean end-to-end, this task can be signed off after review; if not, record the blocker precisely instead of forcing approval.",
    "execution_summary": "## Status\nfailed\n\n## Summary of Changes\n- Created QA tracking task `T20260423-0437`, mock ship task `T20260423-0436`, and follow-up bug `T20260423-0445`.\n- Created a clean disposable git worktree at `/Users/daniel/workspace/repos/orbit-worktrees/T20260423-0437-ship-qa`, verified `--root /Users/daniel/workspace/repos/orbit/.orbit` resolves the canonical task state from that worktree, and validated the clean checkout with `make fmt` and `make build`.\n- Ran the freshly built binary from the QA worktree: `./target/debug/orbit --root /Users/daniel/workspace/repos/orbit/.orbit run ship T20260423-0436 --base agent-main --json`. The command returned run `jrun-20260423-0438` in `failed` state before any worktree setup, implementer execution, push, or PR-open side effects.\n- Inspected the persisted audit/state for `jrun-20260423-0438` and reproduced the hidden underlying error through direct v2 job diagnostics. `orbit job run task_auto_pipeline` surfaced `missing input value for 'max_tasks'`; a second diagnostic with `max_tasks=50` surfaced `missing input value for 'max_bundle_size'`.\n- Root cause: `crates/orbit-engine/src/activity_job/job_executor.rs` only applies `job.default_input` when the caller input is `null`; once `orbit run ship` provides any JSON object at all, unspecified defaults are dropped instead of merged.\n\n## Strategic Decisions\n- Used the freshly built `./target/debug/orbit` binary from the clean worktree rather than the installed `orbit` on PATH | Rationale: ensures the QA exercised the current checkout rather than a stale install.\n- Used direct `orbit job run task_auto_pipeline` diagnostics after the initial `run ship` failure | Rationale: the `run ship` wrapper and persisted `show` path did not surface `JobOutcome.message`, so this was the safest way to recover the concrete failure reason without pushing a workaround through the PR path.\n\n## Validation\n- `make fmt`\n- `make build`\n- `orbit --root /Users/daniel/workspace/repos/orbit/.orbit task show T20260423-0437` from the clean worktree to confirm canonical root resolution\n- `./target/debug/orbit --root /Users/daniel/workspace/repos/orbit/.orbit run ship T20260423-0436 --base agent-main --json` -> failed run `jrun-20260423-0438`\n- `./target/debug/orbit --root /Users/daniel/workspace/repos/orbit/.orbit run ship show jrun-20260423-0438 --json` -> failed run summary with no surfaced message/steps\n- `./target/debug/orbit --root /Users/daniel/workspace/repos/orbit/.orbit job run task_auto_pipeline --json --input mode=pr --input base_branch=agent-main --input 'task_ids=[\\\"T20260423-0436\\\"]'` -> `missing input value for 'max_tasks'`\n- `./target/debug/orbit --root /Users/daniel/workspace/repos/orbit/.orbit job run task_auto_pipeline --json --input mode=pr --input base_branch=agent-main --input max_tasks=50 --input 'task_ids=[\\\"T20260423-0436\\\"]'` -> `missing input value for 'max_bundle_size'`\n\n## Design Weaknesses / Risks\n- `orbit run ship` is currently not sign-offable: the default PR workflow fails before backlog materialization because seeded workflow defaults are not merged with caller input | Severity: High | Mitigation: fix follow-up bug `T20260423-0445`, then rerun this same QA path.\n- The persisted run inspection path (`run ship show` / `job run-state`) does not surface the underlying `JobOutcome.message`, which makes workflow failures materially harder to diagnose | Severity: Medium | Mitigation: include message propagation in `T20260423-0445` or a closely related follow-up.\n\n## Deviations from Original Plan\n- The QA did not reach the mock task's shared worktree / implementer / PR-open phases | Justification: the user-facing command failed in `task_auto_pipeline` before those phases began, and forcing a manual workaround through the rest of the workflow would not count as validating `orbit run ship` itself.\n\n## Recommended Follow-Ups\n- Fix `T20260423-0445` so `job.default_input` merges with explicit caller input objects.\n- After that fix lands, rerun `T20260423-0437`'s exact smoke path against either reopened task `T20260423-0436` or a fresh disposable mock task.\n- Consider exposing `JobOutcome.message` in `orbit run ship show` so workflow failures remain diagnosable without dropping to `orbit job run`.\n\n## Overall Assessment\nOn April 22, 2026 Pacific time (April 23 UTC in Orbit history), the QA pass proved that the advertised `orbit run ship` flow is currently broken. The command fails deterministically before worktree setup because required workflow defaults (`max_tasks`, then `max_bundle_size`) are not inherited from `task_auto_pipeline`'s `default_input`. I did not sign this off.",
