    "execution_summary": "## Status\nfailed\n\n## Summary of Changes\nExecuted an isolated QA pass from `/tmp/orbit-duel-qa-T20260423-0435` using Orbit root `/tmp/orbit-duel-qa-T20260423-0435/.orbit-qa`.\nCreated mock tasks `T20260423-0438` and `T20260423-0438-2` for retired command checks.\nSeeded minimal duel fixtures:\n- `resources/jobs/job_duel_pipeline.yaml`\n- `resources/jobs/job_duel_plan_pipeline.yaml`\n- `state/scoreboard/duel.json`\n- `state/job-runs/job_duel_pipeline/jrun-20260423-qa-duel`\n- `state/job-runs/job_duel_plan_pipeline/jrun-20260423-qa-plan`\n- `state/job-runs/task_local_pipeline/jrun-20260423-qa-other`\n\nCommands exercised:\n- `orbit run duel score --root /tmp/orbit-duel-qa-T20260423-0435/.orbit-qa` on an empty initialized root -> `No duel runs recorded yet.`\n- `orbit run duel T20260423-0438 --root /tmp/orbit-duel-qa-T20260423-0435/.orbit-qa` -> retired workflow error as expected.\n- `orbit run duel plan T20260423-0438-2 --root /tmp/orbit-duel-qa-T20260423-0435/.orbit-qa` -> retired planning workflow error as expected.\n- `orbit run duel score --root /tmp/orbit-duel-qa-T20260423-0435/.orbit-qa` -> aggregated table rendered from mock `duel.json`.\n- `orbit run duel score --json --root /tmp/orbit-duel-qa-T20260423-0435/.orbit-qa` -> JSON payload reported `runs: 2` with expected per-role rows.\n- `orbit run duel score --by ambiguity --role reviewer --json --root /tmp/orbit-duel-qa-T20260423-0435/.orbit-qa` -> reviewer rows segmented as `well_specified` and `needs_judgment`.\n- `orbit run duel list --root /tmp/orbit-duel-qa-T20260423-0435/.orbit-qa` -> listed seeded `duel` and `duel-plan` runs in reverse chronological order.\n- `orbit run duel list --status success --limit 1 --json --root /tmp/orbit-duel-qa-T20260423-0435/.orbit-qa` -> returned only `jrun-20260423-qa-duel`.\n- `orbit run duel show --root /tmp/orbit-duel-qa-T20260423-0435/.orbit-qa` -> showed latest seeded `duel-plan` run with failed step summary.\n- `orbit run duel show jrun-20260423-qa-duel --step 1 --json --root /tmp/orbit-duel-qa-T20260423-0435/.orbit-qa` -> returned the seeded `record_duel_scores` step payload.\n- `orbit run duel show jrun-20260423-qa-other --root /tmp/orbit-duel-qa-T20260423-0435/.orbit-qa` -> rejected a non-duel run with the expected `not a duel pipeline` error.\n\nReal workspace checks:\n- `orbit run duel list` -> `error: job not found: job_duel_pipeline`\n- `orbit run duel show` -> `error: job not found: job_duel_pipeline`\n\n## Overall Assessment\n`orbit run duel` is not ready for sign-off in the real workspace. The retired execution paths communicate the intended contract clearly, and the read-only scoreboard/list/show rendering logic works when supplied with duel job assets plus historical run fixtures. However, the shipped workspace no longer contains duel job assets, so `list` and latest `show` fail before they can inspect history.\n\n## Design Weaknesses / Risks\n- `score` reads duel history directly via `runtime.load_duel_runs`, so it remains usable.\n- `list` and latest `show` still depend on `load_filtered_job_runs` -> `runtime.job_history` -> `load_v2_job_asset_by_name(job_id)`, which hard-fails when `job_duel_pipeline` / `job_duel_plan_pipeline` assets are absent.\n- This leaves the CLI in a partially retired state: help text and retirement messaging promise preserved historical inspection surfaces, but two of those surfaces are broken in the actual workspace.\n\n## Recommended Follow-Ups\n- Restore duel job assets, or decouple `orbit run duel list` and latest `show` from live job-asset lookup so they read stored run bundles directly.\n- Add a regression test covering historical duel state when duel job assets are absent.\n",
