    "description": "## Problem\n\nOnce Orbit has a first-class `orbit mcp init/remove` scaffold, Gemini-specific setup should live under `orbit mcp init --gemini` instead of requiring users to hand-author Gemini MCP config. Gemini CLI supports project-local MCP configuration in `.gemini/settings.json`, so Orbit should be able to seed and remove the Orbit MCP server entry for the current workspace just like it now does for Claude and Codex.\n\n## Why It Matters\n\n- Gemini should participate in the same MCP setup flow as Claude and Codex instead of being a manual follow-up.\n- Project-local Gemini config keeps the integration workspace-scoped rather than mutating global user settings in `~/.gemini/settings.json`.\n- This keeps the happy path coherent: `orbit workspace init` delegates to `orbit mcp init --auto`, and the Gemini portion of that path is implemented here when a repo opts into Gemini.\n\n## Scope\n\n1. **Gemini seeder under `mcp init`** — implement the Gemini-specific branch of `orbit mcp init --gemini` so it creates or updates project-local `.gemini/settings.json` with an Orbit MCP server entry for the current workspace.\n2. **Safe-default server registration** — the generated Gemini config should point at the current supported Orbit MCP command (`orbit serve mcp`) and rely on the server's default safe surface (graph read + stable `orbit.task.*` tools). This task should not add a separate client-side write opt-in path for experimental graph writes.\n3. **Remove path** — implement the Gemini-specific branch of `orbit mcp remove --gemini` so Orbit's Gemini MCP registration can be removed cleanly without disturbing unrelated project config.\n4. **Workspace init delegation** — ensure the Gemini seeder is what runs when `orbit workspace init` delegates to `orbit mcp init --auto` and Gemini is selected.\n\n## Constraints / Notes\n\n- Do **not** modify the user's global `~/.gemini/settings.json`; this should stay workspace-local.\n- Keep unrelated `.gemini/settings.json` content intact when merging or removing the Orbit-owned server entry.\n- Because `.gemini/` will be a local workspace artifact, keep repo ignore/docs behavior consistent with the existing `.claude/` and `.codex/` integrations.\n- This task depends on the shared MCP scaffold/gating task and should not re-invent command parsing or provider selection logic locally.",
