        "message": "## Phase 1 complete — harness core validated (stopped per plan for human review)\n\n**Delivered files:**\n- `benchmarks/graph/scripts/run.sh` + `run.py` — single-cell driver with `--mcp-config + --strict-mcp-config`, `--append-system-prompt` nonce, pre-flight sonnet probe, stream-json tool-call histogram, arm-specific steer, verdict classification.\n- `benchmarks/graph/scripts/sweep.py` — orchestrator, deterministic shuffle, `order.json`, budget ceiling.\n- `benchmarks/graph/scripts/aggregate.py` — primary (arm × task_class) + secondary (model × arm × task_class) markdown tables.\n- `benchmarks/graph/scripts/classify.py` + `oracle.py` — pure-function verdict + oracle dispatch.\n- `benchmarks/graph/scripts/test_classify.py` — 15 unit tests (14 pass, 1 skip on optional fixture).\n- `benchmarks/graph/tasks/locate-agentruntime.yaml` — one exemplar fixture (rest to follow in Phase 2).\n\n**Non-trivial finding — MCP server name collision.** Original `mcp.json` declared server name `orbit`, which collided with the parent workspaces `disabledMcpServers: [\"orbit\"]` entry in `~/.claude.json`. `--strict-mcp-config` did NOT bypass this shadow — child sessions showed `status: disabled` and no graph tools loaded. Renaming to `orbit-bench` (tool prefix `mcp__orbit-bench__*`) fixes it. Filed as friction T20260422-1712.\n\n**Smoke sweep (sweep-id `smoke-v3`, 3 cells, total $0.21):**\n\n| arm | verdict | tokens | cost | notable |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| graph-only | pass | 599 | $0.09 | used orbit_graph_search + orbit_graph_implementors |\n| hybrid | pass | 534 | $0.07 | agent chose Grep (legitimate; classifier now skips the arm-enforcement check for hybrid because filesystem was available) |\n| no-graph | pass | 523 | $0.05 | Grep only |\n\nAll three runs show `claude-sonnet-4-6` + `claude-haiku-4-5-20251001` only — no opus escalation (advisor disabled via `~/.claude/settings.json`).\n\n**Classifier refinement during Phase 1:** the original AC language *\"graph-enabled arms with zero mcp__orbit-bench__* calls and no denials → verdict: error\"* was too strict — it incorrectly penalized hybrid runs where the agent legitimately chose filesystem. The classifier now fires the enforcement-error only when graph is the **exclusive** navigation surface (graph-only arm). Flagging for review in case the AC should be tightened/relaxed to match.\n\n**Remaining work (blocked on human review):**\n- Phase 2: author 17 more fixture YAMLs across locate/trace/edit × easy/medium/hard.\n- Phase 3: `scripts/judge.py` for open-ended trace fixtures.\n- Phase 4: full `N=5` sweep (~270 runs, estimated $10–30 based on smoke throughput) + summary.md.\n\n**Not yet addressed:**\n- Cold-cache nonce effectiveness — the smoke runs showed high `cache_read_tokens` (40K for graph-only) even though each had a fresh nonce in `--append-system-prompt`. This suggests Anthropics cache hits the *prefix* (pre-suffix) rather than the full system prompt, and the nonce is not breaking cache as designed. Needs investigation before Phase 4 — otherwise cache warmth from run ordering contaminates the comparison. May need to spacing-out runs past the 5-min TTL, or using `--exclude-dynamic-system-prompt-sections` + a pre-prompt nonce. Flagging as a Phase 1 incomplete item; does not block Phase 2 authoring.\n- `--output-format stream-json` is the de facto format; JSON single-shot was insufficient for tool-call histogram. Harness ACs were written assuming JSON but the substantive requirement (per-model breakdown, tool_calls histogram) is satisfied.\n\nPer CLAUDE.md, NO commits until human approves. All changes local."
