    "plan": "# Plan\n\nExecution is phased so the paid sweep (~$100s) only runs after the harness is validated and the human has signed off.\n\n## Phase 1 — Harness core (no paid sweep)\n\n1. `benchmarks/graph/scripts/run.sh` — single-cell driver. Responsibilities:\n   - Inputs: `<arm> <task_id> <seed>` plus env `SWEEP_ID`, `RUN_ORDER_INDEX`, `NONCE` (provided by sweep.py).\n   - Fresh nonce injected into the system prompt via `--append-system-prompt` so prompt cache cannot hit.\n   - Invokes `claude -p` with `--mcp-config benchmarks/graph/mcp.json --strict-mcp-config --model sonnet --no-session-persistence --max-budget-usd 1 --output-format json`.\n   - Passes arm-specific `--allowed-tools` / `--disallowed-tools` parsed from `benchmarks/graph/arms/<arm>.json` (prefix rewritten to `mcp__orbit__*`).\n   - Pre-flight probe for graph arms: issues `orbit.graph.overview` call; aborts with `verdict: error` if it fails.\n   - Post-processes `claude -p` JSON into the canonical per-run record under `benchmarks/graph/runs/<arm>/<task_id>/<seed>.json` with keys: `input_tokens`, `cache_read_tokens`, `cache_creation_tokens`, `output_tokens`, `total_cost_usd`, `wall_seconds`, `turns`, `tool_calls`, `verdict`, `transcript_path`, `final_diff_path`, `sweep_id`, `run_order_index`, `nonce`, `model_usage`.\n   - Verdict classification: {pass | fail | error}. `error` when (a) pre-flight probe failed, (b) `claude -p` itself errored, (c) graph-enabled arm with zero `mcp__orbit__*` calls AND empty `permission_denials`, (d) `model_usage` contains `claude-opus-*` or any model outside the infra allowlist (`claude-sonnet-4-*`, `claude-haiku-4-*`). Oracle-based pass/fail happens only for verdicts that arent already `error`.\n   - Oracle evaluation: reads fixture YAML, dispatches to grep/cmd/judge branches; judge fallback invokes `scripts/judge.py`.\n\n2. `benchmarks/graph/scripts/sweep.py` — orchestrator.\n   - Enumerates `(arm, task_id, seed)` for all fixtures under `tasks/*.yaml` and `N` seeds.\n   - Shuffles with `--seed <sweep_seed>` (default: derived from timestamp but recorded).\n   - Writes `benchmarks/graph/runs/_sweeps/<sweep_id>/order.json`.\n   - Launches each cell via `run.sh` serially; collects exit codes; re-runs failed-by-error cells once.\n\n3. `benchmarks/graph/scripts/aggregate.py` — outputs two markdown tables to stdout:\n   - Primary: `(arm, task_class)` x {runs, pass_rate, median/p90 total_tokens, tokens_per_success}.\n   - Secondary: `(model, arm, task_class)` x {cache_read_tokens, output_tokens, cost_usd}.\n\n4. Tests for classification logic (lightweight; Python unittest or bash bats):\n   - Fixture: recorded raw.json with opus in model_usage → verdict=error.\n   - Fixture: recorded raw.json with zero tool calls + empty denials → verdict=error.\n   - Fixture: two back-to-back invocations produce distinct nonces/system-prompt hashes.\n\n5. Smoke test: run the existing `locate-agentruntime` fixture once per arm through `run.sh` + `sweep.py` with a small sweep (3 cells); verify JSON shape + aggregator output. Budget: ~$3.\n\n## Phase 2 — Fixtures (blocked on human review of Phase 1)\n\n6. Author 18 fixture YAMLs under `benchmarks/graph/tasks/`: 6 each × {locate, trace, edit} × {easy, medium, hard}. Mix oracle kinds: grep for locate, cmd (cargo test) for edit, judge for trace.\n\n## Phase 3 — Judge (blocked on Phase 2)\n\n7. `benchmarks/graph/scripts/judge.py` — deterministic judge via direct Anthropic API call using a separate model (e.g. `claude-haiku-4-5` as judge when runs use sonnet; switch to sonnet as judge when runs use haiku). Inputs: fixture path + final-message path. Outputs: exit code 0/1, one-line rationale. Model name from `--judge-model` flag.\n\n## Phase 4 — Paid sweep (blocked on human approval)\n\n8. Execute full `N=5` sweep: `3 arms × 18 tasks × 5 = 270` runs. Rough budget ceiling $150 (some fixtures will be simple/cheap, edit fixtures will be expensive).\n9. Generate `benchmarks/graph/results/<date>-summary.md` with both tables + prose interpretation.\n10. Advance task to review with execution summary.\n\n## Risks\n\n- `--append-system-prompt` may not actually prevent cache hits if Anthropic caches the suffix differently. Mitigation: Phase 1 smoke test checks that back-to-back runs have distinct first-turn `cache_read_tokens` (≈0 for the second run with a fresh nonce). If caching ignores the suffix, fall back to spacing runs past the 5-min TTL.\n- Advisor was disabled in `~/.claude/settings.json` during planning, but child sessions might re-enable via inherited state. The `verdict: error on opus presence` check is the backstop.\n- Budget overrun on edit fixtures. Mitigation: `--max-budget-usd 1` per run; sweep.py aborts if total spend exceeds a configurable ceiling.",
