    "plan": "## Plan\n\n### Overview\nExtend knowledge-graph extraction to non-code files via a trait generalization (`LanguageExtractor` → `FileExtractor`) and three shallow extractors (Markdown, Config, Table). Scope is MVP per task AC — no frontmatter, no nested config paths, no fenced blocks, no semantic indexing.\n\n### Target files\n- `crates/orbit-knowledge/src/extract/language.rs` — replaced/augmented with `FileKind` enum + `FileKind::from_extension`.\n- `crates/orbit-knowledge/src/extract/mod.rs` — `LanguageExtractor` → `FileExtractor`; `ExtractorRegistry::get` by `FileKind`; new extractor modules wired.\n- `crates/orbit-knowledge/src/extract/common.rs` — add `depth: Option<u8>` to `ExtractedLeaf` (feeds `LeafKind::Section { depth }`).\n- `crates/orbit-knowledge/src/graph/nodes.rs` — add `LeafKind::Section { depth: u8 }`, `LeafKind::ConfigKey`, `LeafKind::Column`; update `Display`.\n- `crates/orbit-knowledge/src/pipeline/build.rs` — `parse_leaf_kind` takes depth and maps new kinds; `build_graph_leaves` dispatches by `FileKind` instead of `Language`.\n- Three new modules under `crates/orbit-knowledge/src/extract/`: `markdown.rs`, `config.rs`, `table.rs`.\n- `crates/orbit-knowledge/src/pipeline/scan.rs` — confirm `.md`/`.yaml`/`.yml`/`.json`/`.toml`/`.csv`/`.tsv` are not skipped (they are not today; no change expected).\n- `crates/orbit-knowledge/Cargo.toml` — add `serde_yaml` (workspace has 0.9).\n- `crates/orbit-knowledge/src/service/callers.rs`, `service/implementors.rs` — verify non-code leaves are filtered out (they only match Function/Method/Trait/Impl, so additive).\n- `docs/design/knowledge-graph/4_decisions.md` — ADR-011 (Accepted) describing the generalization + new variants + T20260422-1540 citation.\n\n### Implementation order\n1. Add `FileKind`/`DocFormat`/`ConfigFormat`/`TableFormat` enums + `from_extension`. Unit tests in `language.rs`.\n2. Extend `LeafKind` with `Section { depth }`, `ConfigKey`, `Column`. Update `Display` + any exhaustive matches.\n3. Extend `ExtractedLeaf` with `depth: Option<u8>`.\n4. Rename trait + update registry. Ensure all 5 code extractors still compile.\n5. Implement `MarkdownExtractor` — ATX headings only; slug disambiguation by line number; span = this-heading-line through (exclusive of) next same-or-higher heading.\n6. Implement `ConfigExtractor` — YAML/JSON/TOML; top-level map entries only; non-map roots → 0 leaves.\n7. Implement `TableExtractor` — CSV/TSV header row; 1 MiB cap short-circuits before parsing.\n8. Wire new extractors into `ExtractorRegistry::new`.\n9. Update `build_graph_leaves` to dispatch by `FileKind` (the language column filter widens to any non-Unknown FileKind).\n10. Add unit tests: one per extractor with inline `&str` fixtures.\n11. Add integration-style assertion that history walker populates `task_ids` on new leaves unchanged.\n12. ADR-011 in `4_decisions.md`; bump `Last updated`.\n13. Validation: `make fmt` + `make build`.\n\n### Risks\n- `LeafKind::Section { depth }` changes JSON shape for that variant (struct-variant externally-tagged). Readers pinned to a string-only LeafKind deserializer would fail; no such readers today.\n- `#[non_exhaustive]` not currently on `LeafKind`; any downstream exhaustive match outside the crate would break. Scope of the crate: not yet exposed as a stable public API.\n- CSV 1 MiB cap is a literal const — deliberate per AC, not user-configurable.\n- `depth` field on `ExtractedLeaf` introduces a lightly-exercised optional field; unit-tested.\n\n### Validation\n- Per-extractor unit tests (inline fixtures).\n- `FileKind::from_extension` unit test covers all required extensions + unknown.\n- `make build && make fmt` green.\n- Integration verification (optional stretch): a synthetic workspace with one `.md`, `.yaml`, `.csv` file; run `orbit graph build` and grep the output JSON for the new kinds.\n",
