    "plan": "## Plan\n\n1. Draft the prescriptive spec at `docs/design/knowledge-graph/specs/graph-operations.md` covering all 7 task sections: operation taxonomy, canonical JSON schema, symbol addressing (stable graph-level node IDs — decision locked in), validation rules, producer surface sketch (one call + payload per op), backfill policy, open questions.\n2. Add `ADR-010 — Orbit-owned symbol-level write operations` to `docs/design/knowledge-graph/4_decisions.md` with status `Proposed`, cite T20260421-0543, flag the stable-ID decision + taxonomy.\n3. Bump `Last updated:` on `4_decisions.md`.\n4. Validation: run `make fmt` (no-op for pure docs but honors project policy); grep the new spec to confirm each of the 7 sections has a heading; confirm Task References cites T20260421-0528.\n\n### Path deviation from task spec\nTask names `docs/design/graph-operations.md`. CONVENTIONS.md §2 forbids top-level design docs outside feature folders; §6 defines the correct home: `docs/design/<feature>/specs/<mechanism>.md`. Graph operations are a mechanism of the knowledge graph, not a standalone feature. Landing at `docs/design/knowledge-graph/specs/graph-operations.md`.\n\n### Risks\n- Stable-ID shape is a new field on `BaseNodeFields`; spec calls it a schema change gated behind the producer task, not landing in this task.\n- Spec concision: cap ~500 lines; over-specifying invites drift before the producer exists.\n- Validation of a producer-authored log against the tree diff is load-bearing; spec picks a divergence policy but flags edge cases as open questions.",
