    "description": "## Problem\n\n`list_backlog_tasks` in `crates/orbit-core/src/runtime/v2_host.rs:185` filters out backlog task groups whose `context_files` overlap with files held by `InProgress`/`Review` tasks (see T20260420-0014). The filter works but is invisible: the action returns `{task_count, task_ids, tasks}` and silently drops the rest.\n\nWhen the `dispatch_agent` step receives a shrunken backlog, there is no audit trail explaining *why* certain tasks are missing. The downstream `gate.starvation` audit only fires for tasks that reach the gate, so pre-gate exclusions are invisible to scoreboards and to operators debugging \"why isnt task X being picked up\".\n\nT20260420-0014 description called this out as an optional output-shape extension; it was deferred for that task and is now its own follow-up.\n\n## Why It Matters\n\n- Operators currently cannot tell, from the `dispatch_agent` trace alone, whether a backlog task was filtered for context-lock conflict, type=friction, or simply truncated by `max_tasks`.\n- Scoreboards/audits over the dispatch pipeline would benefit from a single source of truth for pre-gate exclusion reasons.\n- Without this, debugging a starved task requires reading task lock state at audit time and re-running the overlap logic by hand.\n\n## Constraints / Notes\n\n- Output shape change must be **additive** and non-breaking: existing consumers reading `task_count`/`task_ids`/`tasks` must continue to work.\n- The `excluded` field should be an array of objects, each with: `id` (string), `reason` (enum: `context_lock_conflict` | `group_member_conflict`), and `conflicts` (array of objects containing the requesting `context_file` and the locking task id whose file it overlaps).\n- `group_member_conflict` is for backlog tasks dropped because a sibling under the same root ancestor conflicts (the dropped task itself does not directly overlap).\n- `context_lock_conflict` is for the directly-overlapping task.\n- Do NOT include exclusions for `type: friction` or `max_tasks` truncation — scope this strictly to the lock-overlap filter introduced in T20260420-0014.\n- Reuse `task_overlaps_locked_files` and `task_root_id` helpers already in `v2_host.rs` rather than duplicating logic.\n- The `excluded` list should be omitted (not present) when the explicit `task_ids` input path is taken, since that path skips the filter entirely.\n- Update the activity description in `crates/orbit-core/assets/activities/list_backlog_tasks.yaml` to document the new field.",
